    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XI.29</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>74</citedRange></bibl> (fig. 64);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>096800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020"/>, p. <citedRange>245-248</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">τὰ</supplied>ν 
                    <w lemma="ὀπά">ὀπά<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
    </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Un tel a consacré</supplied>la porte.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-so dedicated</supplied> the door.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale ha dedicato</supplied> la porta.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
	           <p>This stone is known only from Oliverio's photograph and transcription. We deduce the date of find from the number of Oliverio's notebook.</p> 
                <p>Pugliese Carratelli in <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>74</citedRange></bibl> supposed that it might be the same stone as
	           <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr020700</ref>, which is a marble epistylium, much larger than this fragment.</p>
	           <p>There are different dedications of monumental doors (<foreign xml:lang="grc">ὀπά</foreign>) in the sanctuary of Apollo, offered by one or several individuals (see 
	               <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015b"/>, p. <citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
